Rakuen's connection to the Great Oasis is primarily through community oral tradition preserved by Khenari and Khephari community members tracing family origin to the desert corridor. The Deepwell Confluence in Rakuen oral tradition is the site where the oasis civilization's administrative genius and its fatal dependencies coexisted: the High Water Court was simultaneously the most sophisticated resource-arbitration institution in the region and the institution most vulnerable to exactly the hydrology failure it was designed to manage. Desert-origin goods reaching Rakuen via Mafdet and coastal routes bear oasis provenance attestations; oasis access disruptions appear downstream as price increases in preserved desert goods.

