Deltari application of Reed Law at the Great Oasis produces a specific jurisdictional reading: the Charter of Passage is the foundational desert-water-right document in Deltari legal tradition. Reed Law treats the oasis as the canonical case where water-right law was correctly formalized and then catastrophically violated by the three-faction collapse. The Pragmatist faction's position — ration to preserve remaining springs — is Reed Law's standard response to scarcity. The Legalist faction's position — Charter of Passage rights are absolute regardless of supply — is Reed Law's liability nightmare: rights that cannot be scaled to supply levels produce exactly the Battle of the Dry Basin outcome. Deltari in Midgaard track Spring Warden communications as the most current oasis hydrology evidence, and treat Spring Wardens as the only faction operating within Reed Law principles.

